In JS code there is a small mistake in stub generated code causing the code to crash even with no modification:

``` var inputs = readline().split(' ');
const diskSize = parseFloat(inputs[0]); // The amount of space left on the disk
const diskUnit = inputs[1];
var inputs = readline().split(' ');
const fileSize = parseFloat(inputs[0]); // The size of the downloaded file
const fileUnit = inputs[1]; ```

inputs is declared two times.

Really good for the rest, i'll approve.

On a personal point of view, it might be a little too complicated for "shortest" mode, lot of times will be spent in coding and not golfing.
